This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on text modelling using VAE-RNN architectures. Additionally, the paper discusses the issue of latent variable collapse, which is a common problem in VAEs used for text modelling. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper proposes a new architecture for VAEs, which could potentially involve neural networks and optimization techniques, making it relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper discusses the quality of generated text, which could involve computer vision techniques for evaluating the text, making it relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
